After his 1996 experience, he declined to play in international competition. He was angered by being overlooked for the 1999 FIBA AmeriCup squad, saying it was a "lack of respect".[128] He forwent an opportunity to participate in the 2000 Olympics, explaining that two gold medals were enough.[129] Shaq also chose not to play in the 2002 FIBA World Championship.[130] He rejected an offer to play in the 2004 Olympics,[131] and although he was initially interested in being named for 2006â€“2008 US preliminary roster,[132] he eventually declined the invitation.[133]
